===誤報歐盟支持香港政改方案===
於2015年5－6月，香港立法會審議[[2016年及2017年香港政治制度改革|政改方案]]，至6月5日，中國日報報道歐盟支持有關方案，但同日即被歐盟駐港澳辦事處去信反駁。<ref name="EUOfficial">{{cite web |author1=Vincent Piket |title=Note to the editor of China Daily Hong Kong edition |url=http://eeas.europa.eu/archives/delegations/hong_kong/documents/news/5_june_2015_note_the_editor_of_china_daily_hong_kong_edition.pdf |accessdate=2020-06-05 |archive-date=2019-08-18 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818203317/http://eeas.europa.eu/archives/delegations/hong_kong/documents/news/5_june_2015_note_the_editor_of_china_daily_hong_kong_edition.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>
===反送中運動期間發報抹黑消息===
因應[[反對逃犯條例修訂草案運動|反對逃犯條例修訂草案運動]]，中國日報香港版的facebook專頁曾於9月9日晚發佈一訊息，指香港的反政府狂熱分子將於9月11日（即美國[[九一一袭击事件|九一一袭击事件]]同日）發動類似的[[恐怖襲擊|恐怖襲擊]]，當中包括炸毀天然氣管道、無差別地攻擊非以廣東話為母語的人士及放火燒山等，並配以美國911事件雙塔焚毀時的圖片<ref>{{cite web |title=反送中》又造假新聞？ 中共黨媒：示威者將發動港版911 |url=https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/2911946 |publisher=自由時報 |accessdate=2019-09-12 |archive-date=2020-06-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200602170933/https://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/2911946 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author1=Sarah Zheng |title=China Daily newspaper criticised over claim Hong Kong protesters are planning 9/11 terror attack |url=https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3026563/china-daily-newspaper-criticised-over-claim-hong-kong |publisher=South China Morning Post |accessdate=2019-09-12 |archive-date=2020-11-12 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112023808/https://www.scmp.com/news/china/diplomacy/article/3026563/china-daily-newspaper-criticised-over-claim-hong-kong |dead-url=no }}</ref>。但有關報導並沒有任何可靠的來源支持，而且此做法亦與中國官方媒體常以恐怖分子等手法來標籤來自香港的抗爭者的手法相類似<ref>{{cite web |title=Hong Kong protesters hit pause to mark Sept. 11 attacks |url=https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/article/2001341530/hong-kong-protesters-hit-pause-to-mark-sept-11-attacks |publisher=Standard Digital |accessdate=2019-09-12 |archive-date=2019-09-13 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190913183906/https://www.standardmedia.co.ke/article/2001341530/hong-kong-protesters-hit-pause-to-mark-sept-11-attacks |dead-url=no }}</ref>。不少抗爭者因應有關消息，均發佈會於9月11日當天暫停抗爭活動，並會為美國911事件中對抗恐襲人士致以敬意<ref>{{cite web |author1=BILLIE THOMSON FOR MAILONLINE |title=Chinese state newspaper is blasted for claiming that Hong Kong protesters will stage a '9/11 terror plot' with a photo of the burning Twin Towers in a social media post |url=https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-7451253/Chinese-state-newspaper-claims-Hong-Kong-protesters-stage-9-11-terror-plot.html |publisher=Daily Mail |accessdate=2019-09-12 |archive-date=2020-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127112854/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-7451253/Chinese-state-newspaper-claims-Hong-Kong-protesters-stage-9-11-terror-plot.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

